1. Create a .gitignore file in your project root directory:
node_modules/
.env
.DS_Store
*.log
dist/
build/
coverage/
.vscode/
.idea/
2. If you already committed node_modules, remove it:
bash# Remove node_modules from Git tracking
git rm -r --cached node_modules

# Add .gitignore
git add .gitignore

# Commit the changes
git commit -m "Remove node_modules and add .gitignore"

# Push to GitHub
git push origin main
