# OS
4. Quick Setup Command:
bash# Create .gitignore file
echo "node_modules/" > .gitignore

# Initialize git (if not already done)
git init

# Add all files except node_modules
git add .

# Commit
git commit -m "Initial commit"

# Add remote and push
git remote add origin <your-github-repo-url>
git push -u origin main
5. Important Notes:

✅ Always create .gitignore BEFORE your first commit
✅ Include package.json and package-lock.json (so others can install dependencies)
✅ Others will run npm install to get their own node_modules
❌ Never commit .env files 